<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06025r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06025r">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06025r"> 25(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mt of God open to shelter BVM</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">But Elisabeth, having heard that they were searching for John, took him and went up into the hill country, and kept looking where to conceal him. Now there was no place of concealment, and she was weary. And groaning, with a loud voice, she said, &ldquo;O mountain of God, receive a mother and child unjustly pursued.&rdquo; And God sent the archangel Uriel; and he commanded the mountain to open. And immediately <mark>the mountain was cleft, and received them within</mark>. <small> James DeQincy Donehoo, <a name="APOCD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#APOCD"><cite title="source">Les The Apocryphal Life of Christ</cite></a> (1903) 79</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01098a" href="c01all.htm#c01098a">VI.C.01:098(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
